ion:United States - California - Foster City</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Functional Area:Finance</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Position Type:Regular</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Working Hours:Full Time</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Apply NowEmail a friend</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Specific Responsibilities</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Gilead is seeking a Senior Accounting Manager to lead General</p><p>Ledger operations for North America. The Senior Accounting Manager will lead a team of Senior Accountants, and partner with various groups including: FP&amp;A, Facilities, Treasury, Controllership, and other Business Partners. The Senior Accounting Manager is experienced in leading process changes and leveraging technology to enhance the efficiency and accuracy of the month-end close processes. The position requires the</p><p>individual to have the ability to effectively multi-task, prioritize work,</p><p>demonstrate accountability, and lead a team of accounting professionals to support US and Canada General Ledger accounting activities. The Senior Accounting Manager will also</p><p>ensure systems, processes and controls are compliant with SOX and US GAAP requirements.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Essential Duties and Job Functions</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Overall responsibility for providing timely, accurate, and comprehensive accounting, reconciliation, and reporting relating to FP&amp;A accruals, cash, prepaids, deferred rent, leases, allocations, reclassifications, etc.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Maintain ownership of the Assurenet/Cadency account reconciliation software. This includes providing support to broader North America accounting teams for questions, new account assignments, etc.. Perform a reconciliation of global Assurenet balances to the General Ledger.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Lead the closing of the Oracle Projects Module during the month-end close. Support Oracle Projects and Oracle GL testing as required to support business process changes and IT upgrades.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Thorough review of journal entries, following up with requestors for any additional support or understandings if necessary. Ensure accrual balances are reviewed and supported.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Review and approve monthly balance sheet account reconciliations per the assigned deadlines, ensuring that any reconciling items are cleared on a timely basis.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Ensure GAAP, Sarbanes-Oxley requirements, finance policies (Controllerâs Manual), and tax and legal requirements are followed.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Develop, implement, and maintain policies, procedures, controls and systems to ensure process/policy changes are implemented, and transactions are properly accounted for.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Identify areas for process improvement and efficiencies, and drive solutions focusing on global standardization.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Maintain a great working relationship with all business partners. Provide accounting guidance and training to staff and business partners as required. Review accruals with FP&amp;A business partners in advance of the quarter closes.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Provide support for internal and external audits.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Knowledge, Experience and Skills</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ 8+ years of relevant experience and a BA or BS degree in accounting or equivalent.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ 2+ years of previous supervisory experience is required.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ A track record of successfully leading and developing people.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Ability to build strong partnerships with key business stakeholders and work cross functionally.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Ability to identify and drive sustained process improvement, automation, solving complex problems.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Excellent communication skills, organization skills, multi-tasking and prioritizing skills.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Demonstrated technical, problem solving, and analytical skills.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Ability to navigate complex processes involving multiple systems.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Working knowledge of Oracle R12 or similar integrated software product is necessary.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Ability to act independently, be self-motivated, and motivate others.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ A highly collaborative style that works with all levels of leadership.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Proficiency with Microsoft tools (Outlook, Word, and Intermediate Excel) is required.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Strong written, presentation and interpersonal skills are required.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Able to work in a fast-paced, multi-national, changing environment, meeting deadlines in an accurate and timely manner. Must be detail-oriented.</p><br /><br /><div style="text-align:left;padding-bottom: 20px;"><a href="/frca-apply/bjvwvs" id="ApplyBottomLink" target="_blank" class="bigBlueButtonLink" rel="nofollow" onclick="javascript:setTimeout(&quot;window.location.href = &#39;/post-resume?jid=bjvwvs&#39;;&quot;,1500); return true;">Go to apply&nbsp;<img src="/Images/applyarrow.png" height="21x;" width="16px;" alt="" /></a></div></div></div></div><div style="background-color: #fcfcfc; max-width: 400px;" class="sideBar"><div style="text-align:left; vertical-align:top; padding-left:5px;"><h4 style="padding-bottom:7px;">Similar Jobs</h4><p style="padding-bottom:4px;"><a href="/job/bju0r8/accounting-manager-fp-san-francisco-ca" rel="nofollow" onclick="ga(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;Links&#39;, &#39;JobToJob&#39;, &#39;0&#39;);">Accounting Manager</a><br/><span style="font-size:small" class="colorLocation">San Francisco, CA</span><span style="font-size:small;color:black"> - ac